TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Let \( f(x)=-x^2+3x \) on the interval \( [1,3] \). Find the absolute maximum and absolute minimum of \( f(x) \) on this interval. $BR
$BR
The absolute max occurs at \(x=\)\{ans_rule(15)\}.$BR
The absolute min occurs at \(x=\)\{ans_rule(15)\}.$BR
EOT

$ans1 = 3/2;
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
$ans2 = 3;
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));

